
Step 1: Create the DynamoDB Table
AWS Console Method
Login to the AWS Management Console.
Navigate to DynamoDB → Tables → Create Table.
Configure the table:
Table name: datacenter-tasks
Primary key: taskId (String)
Leave other settings as default for now (provisioned capacity, encryption, etc.)
Click Create Table.
Wait until the table status shows Active.
AWS CLI Method
aws dynamodb create-table \
    --table-name datacenter-tasks \
    --attribute-definitions AttributeName=taskId,AttributeType=S \
    --key-schema AttributeName=taskId,KeyType=HASH \
    --provisioned-throughput ReadCapacityUnits=5,WriteCapacityUnits=5
Wait until the table status is ACTIVE.
Step 2: Insert Tasks into the Table
AWS CLI Method
Task 1:

aws dynamodb put-item \
    --table-name datacenter-tasks \
    --item '{"taskId": {"S": "1"}, "description": {"S": "Learn DynamoDB"}, "status": {"S": "completed"}}'

